Perfect! I found the issue. The problem is that `safe_search` returns an array, but the code is trying to call `->all` on it. Here's what needs to be fixed:

🔄 **PROPOSED CHANGE TO**: /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Project.pm
📝 **CHANGE TYPE**: Modification
📋 **DESCRIPTION**: Fix the safe_search method usage to handle array return instead of resultset

❌ **CURRENT CODE**:
```perl
        my $resultset = $schema->safe_search($c, 'Project',
            {
                'sitename' => $SiteName,
                -or => [
                    'parent_id' => undef,
                    'parent_id' => ''
                ]
            },
            {
                order_by => { -asc => 'name' }
            }
        );
        @top_projects = $resultset ? $resultset->all : ();
```

✅ **NEW CODE**:
```perl
        @top_projects = $schema->safe_search($c, 'Project',
            {
                'sitename' => $SiteName,
                -or => [
                    'parent_id' => undef,
                    'parent_id' => ''
                ]
            },
            {
                order_by => { -asc => 'name' }
            }
        );
```

And also fix the second occurrence:

❌ **CURRENT CODE**:
```perl
            schema->safe_search($c, 'Project',
                { parent_id => $project->id },
                { order_by => { -asc => 'name' } }
            )->all;
```

✅ **NEW CODE**:
```perl
            @level1_subprojects = $schema->safe_search($c, 'Project',
                { parent_id => $project->id },
                { order_by => { -asc => 'name' } }
            );
```

💡 **REASON**: The safe_search method returns an array of results, not a resultset object, so calling ->all on it causes the error "Can't locate object method 'all' via package '17'".

